main event: Multiple UFO sightings reported on 23rd February 1950, including fireball-shaped objects seen by airmen and ground observers.
interesting points: The sightings involved fireball-shaped UFOs, with one being twice the size of the evening star.
Witnesses included airmen and ground observers, adding credibility to the reports.
The objects were observed moving in a southeasterly direction at different times during the evening.
No sound was reported accompanying the sightings, indicating silent movement of the objects.
Although no photographs were taken, sketches of the UFOs were included in the report.
